'''Hacho Kirilov Boyadzhiev''' ({{lang-bg|<U+0425><U+0430><U+0447><U+043E> <U+041A><U+0438><U+0440><U+0438><U+043B><U+043E><U+0432> <U+0411><U+043E><U+044F><U+0434><U+0436><U+0438><U+0435><U+0432>}}; b. 20 January 1932)<ref name=imdb>{{cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1017674/#director1970|title=Hacho Boyadzhiev |publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=2008-10-18}}</ref> is a [[Bulgaria]]n television director|television]] and [[film director]].

Boyadzhiev was born in [[Sofia]]<ref name=imdb/> under the name Imre as the [[illegitimate child|illegitimate]] son of car racer and [[Bohemianism|bohemian]] Dimitar Sokolov and 17-year-old [[Hungarians|Hungarian]] emigrant mother Piri,<ref name=standart>{{cite news|url=http://paper.standartnews.com/archive/2003/12/27/interview/index.htm|title=<U+0425><U+0430><U+0447><U+043E>: <U+0414><U+0430><U+0434><U+043E><U+0445> <U+043D><U+0430> <U+0434><U+0435><U+0446><U+0430><U+0442><U+0430> <U+0441><U+0438> <U+043D><U+0435><U+043C><U+0441><U+043A><U+043E> <U+0432><U+044A><U+0437><U+043F><U+0438><U+0442><U+0430><U+043D><U+0438><U+0435> (<U+0438><U+043D><U+0442><U+0435><U+0440><U+0432><U+044E>)|last=<U+0413><U+043E><U+0437><U+0435><U+0441>|first=<U+0418><U+0441><U+0430><U+043A>|date=2003-12-27|publisher=''<U+0421><U+0442><U+0430><U+043D><U+0434><U+0430><U+0440><U+0442>''|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=2008-10-18}}</ref> a [[milliner]].<ref name=trud>{{cite news|title=<U+041C><U+0430><U+0439><U+043A><U+0430> <U+043C><U+0438> <U+043F><U+0430><U+0437><U+0438> <U+043A><U+043B><U+0435><U+0442><U+0432><U+0430> <U+0434><U+0430> <U+043D><U+0435> <U+043C><U+0435> <U+0432><U+0438><U+0436><U+0434><U+0430> 35 <U+0433><U+043E><U+0434><U+0438><U+043D><U+0438> (<U+0438><U+043D><U+0442><U+0435><U+0440><U+0432><U+044E>)|last=<U+041F><U+0435><U+0442><U+043A><U+043E><U+0432><U+0430>|first=<U+0412><U+0430><U+043B><U+0435><U+043D><U+0442><U+0438><U+043D><U+0430>|date=2008-10-18|publisher=''<U+0422><U+0440><U+0443><U+0434>''|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=2008-10-18}}</ref> However, his mothers' parents did not approve their relationship. He was adopted by the [[Novi Pazar, Bulgaria|Novi Pazar]] merchant Kiril Boyadzhiev, whom he considers his real father, when he was six months old; the document was issued in [[Skopje]]. Until the death of his adoptive father, he didn't see his Hungarian mother by birth.<ref name=trud/>

Boyadzhiev spent his childhood in Novi Pazar and then enrolled in the [[Augustine of Hippo|Saint Augustine]] [[France|French]] college in [[Plovdiv]]. During the [[Allied bombing]]s of the city in 1943, he returned to Novi Pazar.<ref name=standart/> In 1951, he began studying [[mathematics]] at [[Sofia University]] but soon moved to the [[Krastyo Sarafov National Academy for Theatre and Film Arts|National Academy for Theatre and Film Arts]] to study directing.<ref name=trud/>

After graduating and heading the [[Vidin]] Theatre<ref name=jobs>{{cite news|url=http://jobs.bg/magazine/29|title="<U+0421><U+0435><U+0433><U+0430> <U+043D><U+0430><U+0446><U+0438><U+043E><U+043D><U+0430><U+043B><U+043D><U+0430><U+0442><U+0430> <U+0442><U+0435><U+043B><U+0435><U+0432><U+0438><U+0437><U+0438><U+044F> <U+0435> <U+0435><U+0434><U+043D><U+0430> <U+0437><U+0430><U+0441><U+043F><U+0430><U+043B><U+0430> <U+043C><U+0435><U+0447><U+043A><U+0430>. <U+0427><U+0430><U+043A><U+0430><U+043C> <U+0434><U+0435><U+043D><U+044F>, <U+043A><U+043E><U+0433><U+0430><U+0442><U+043E> <U+0449><U+0435> <U+0441><U+0435> <U+0441><U+044A><U+0431><U+0443><U+0434><U+0438>"|last=<U+0427><U+0435><U+0448><U+043C><U+0435><U+0434><U+0436><U+0438><U+0435><U+0432><U+0430>|first=<U+0410><U+043B><U+0431><U+0435><U+043D><U+0430>|date=2006-09-11|publisher=<U+0421><U+043F><U+0438><U+0441><U+0430><U+043D><U+0438><U+0435> Jobs.bg|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=2008-10-18}}</ref> Boyadzhiev went to [[Beirut]], [[Lebanon]] after an invitation by a fellow student. In Lebanon, he suffered a severe [[Car accident|car crash]] due to a [[drugs|drugged]] [[taxi]] driver; of the six people in the car died, only Boyadzhiev survived, although with a broken [[Vertebral column|backbone]]. After his rehabilitation he worked as a make-up man for an [[Arabic language|Arabic]] movie. At age 28<U+2013>29, he moved to [[Paris]], France by becoming a greaser on a Beirut<U+2013>[[Marseille]] [[steamship]]. In France he was a waiter in a [[bistro]]; it was at the bistro that he met filmmaker [[Ren<U+00E9> Clair]] and worked as his assistant for three years.<ref name=trud/>

Boyadzhiev has also worked in [[New York City]] in the [[United States]]; he has also been to [[Canada]] (as a [[CBS]] correspondent)<ref name=jobs/> and [[Hollywood]] and took his doctor's degree in cinema and television studied from the [[University of Cambridge]]. In 1963<U+2013>1964, he started working with the [[Bulgarian National Television]] as a news director: among the best-known television programmes he has directed are ''Flight Over the Night'' and [[Todor Kolev (actor)|Todor Kolev]]'s ''How are we Going to Catch up with the Americans<U+2026>?''.<ref name=trud/> From 1993 to 1995, he headed the Bulgarian National Television;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bnt.bg/content/view/full/790/|title=<U+0418><U+0441><U+0442><U+043E><U+0440><U+0438><U+044F> <U+043D><U+0430> <U+0411><U+041D><U+0422>: <U+0425><U+0430><U+0447><U+043E> <U+0411><U+043E><U+044F><U+0434><U+0436><U+0438><U+0435><U+0432> (11.03.1993 - 23.06.1995)|publisher=<U+0411><U+044A><U+043B><U+0433><U+0430><U+0440><U+0441><U+043A><U+0430> <U+043D><U+0430><U+0446><U+0438><U+043E><U+043D><U+0430><U+043B><U+043D><U+0430> <U+0442><U+0435><U+043B><U+0435><U+0432><U+0438><U+0437><U+0438><U+044F>|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=2008-10-18}}</ref> in 1971<U+2013>1979, he had been the television's head director He has been married two times and has seven daughters, most from women he has not been married to. Three were born in Bulgaria and bear his family name, two were born in the United States, one in France and one in [[England]].<ref name=standart/>

==Filmography==
* ''Macbeth'' (1978)
* ''This Fine Age of Maturity'' (1985)
* ''The Man on the Road'' (1987)<ref name=imdb/>

